   EXECUTIVE BRANCH

   The power of the Executive Branch is vested in the President, who also
   serves as Commander in Chief of the Armed Forces. The President
   appoints the Cabinet and oversees the various agencies and departments
   of the federal government.

   Executive Office Of The President

   The Executive Office of the President (EOP) serves the Presidentin the
   performance of the many detailed activities incident to his immediate
   office. The staff of the President facilitates and maintains
   communication with the Congress, the individual Members of the
   Congress, the heads of executive agencies, the press and other
   information media, and the general public. The various Assistants to
   the President assist the President in such matters as he may direct.

